    <p>{`Vector maintains the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://hub.docker.com/r/timberio/vector"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`timberio/vector`}</inlineCode>{` Docker images`}</a>{`
available on `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://hub.docker.com/r/timberio/vector"
      }}>{`Docker Hub`}</a>{` which come pre-installed
with Vector and any recommended system dependencies. These images are available
for x86_64, ARM64, and ARMv7
architectures.`}</p>
    {
      /*
          THIS FILE IS AUTOGENERATED!
           To make changes please edit the template located at:
           website/docs/setup/installation/platforms/docker.md.erb
      */
    }
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "install"
    }}>{`Install`}</h2>
    <Tabs block={true} defaultValue="daemon" values={[{
      "label": "As a Daemon",
      "value": "daemon"
    }, {
      "label": "As a Sidecar",
      "value": "sidecar"
    }, {
      "label": "As a Service",
      "value": "service"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="daemon" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/setup/deployment/strategies/#daemon"
          }}>{`daemon deployment strategy`}</a>{` is designed for data
collection on a single host. Vector runs in the background, in its own process,
collecting `}<em parentName="p">{`all`}</em>{` data for that host.
Typically data is collected from a process manager, such as Journald via
Vector's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/journald/"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`journald`}</inlineCode>{` source`}</a>{`, but can be collected
through any of Vector's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/"
          }}>{`sources`}</a>{`.
The following diagram demonstrates how it works.`}</p>
        <DaemonDiagram platformName={"docker"} sourceName={null} sinkName={null} mdxType="DaemonDiagram" />
        <hr></hr>
        <Tabs centered={true} className={"rounded"} defaultValue={"docker-cli"} placeholder="Please choose an installation method..." select={false} size={null} values={[{
          "group": "Platforms",
          "label": "Docker CLI",
          "value": "docker-cli"
        }, {
          "group": "Platforms",
          "label": "Docker Compose",
          "value": "docker-compose"
        }]} mdxType="Tabs">
          <TabItem value="docker-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
            <Steps headingDepth={3} mdxType="Steps">
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <h3 {...{
                    "id": "configure-vector"
                  }}>{`Configure Vector`}</h3>
                  <ConfigExample format="toml" path={"/etc/vector/vector.toml"} sourceName={"docker"} sinkName={null} mdxType="ConfigExample" />
                </li>
                <li>
                  <h3 {...{
                    "id": "start-the-vector-container"
                  }}>{`Start the Vector container`}</h3>
                  <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
                      "className": "language-bash"
                    }}>{`docker run \\
  -v $PWD/vector.toml:/etc/vector/vector.toml:ro \\
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\
  timberio/vector:latest-alpine
`}</code></pre>
                  <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
                    <ul>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`-v $PWD/vector.to...`}</inlineCode>{` flag passes your custom configuration to Vector.`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`-v /var/run/docke...`}</inlineCode>{` flag ensures that Vector has access to the Docker API.`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`timberio/vector:latest-alpine`}</inlineCode>{` is the default image we've chosen, you are welcome to use `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                          "href": "/docs/setup/installation/platforms/docker/#variants"
                        }}>{`other image variants`}</a>{`.`}</li>
                    </ul>
                  </CodeExplanation>
                  <p>{`That's it! Simple and to the point. Hit `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`ctrl+c`}</inlineCode>{` to exit.`}</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </Steps>
          </TabItem>
          <TabItem value="docker-compose" mdxType="TabItem">
            <p>{`compose!`}</p>
          </TabItem>
        </Tabs>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="sidecar" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/setup/deployment/strategies/#sidecar"
          }}>{`sidecar deployment strategy`}</a>{` is designed to
collect data from a `}<em parentName="p">{`single`}</em>{` service. Vector has a tight 1 to 1 coupling with
each service. Typically data is collected by tailing local files via Vector's
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/file/"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`file`}</inlineCode>{` source`}</a>{`, but can be collected through any of Vector's
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/"
          }}>{`sources`}</a>{`. The following diagram demonstrates how it works.`}</p>
        <SidecarDiagram platformName={"docker"} sourceName={null} sinkName={null} mdxType="SidecarDiagram" />
        <hr></hr>
        <Tabs centered={true} className={"rounded"} defaultValue={"docker-cli"} placeholder="Please choose an installation method..." select={false} size={null} values={[{
          "group": "Platforms",
          "label": "Docker CLI",
          "value": "docker-cli"
        }, {
          "group": "Platforms",
          "label": "Docker Compose",
          "value": "docker-compose"
        }]} mdxType="Tabs">
          <TabItem value="docker-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
            <Steps headingDepth={3} mdxType="Steps">
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <h3 {...{
                    "id": "configure-vector-1"
                  }}>{`Configure Vector`}</h3>
                  <ConfigExample format="toml" path={"/etc/vector/vector.toml"} sourceName={"file"} sinkName={null} mdxType="ConfigExample" />
                </li>
                <li>
                  <h3 {...{
                    "id": "start-the-vector-container-1"
                  }}>{`Start the Vector container`}</h3>
                  <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
                      "className": "language-bash"
                    }}>{`docker run \\
  -v $PWD/vector.toml:/etc/vector/vector.toml:ro \\
  -v /var/log \\
  timberio/vector:latest-alpine
`}</code></pre>
                  <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
                    <ul>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`-v $PWD/vector.to...`}</inlineCode>{` flag passes your custom configuration to Vector.`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`-v /var/log`}</inlineCode>{` flag ensures that Vector has access to your app's logging directory, adjust as necessary.`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`timberio/vector:latest-alpine`}</inlineCode>{` is the default image we've chosen, you are welcome to use `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                          "href": "/docs/setup/installation/platforms/docker/#variants"
                        }}>{`other image variants`}</a>{`.`}</li>
                    </ul>
                  </CodeExplanation>
                  <p>{`That's it! Simple and to the point. Hit `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`ctrl+c`}</inlineCode>{` to exit.`}</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </Steps>
          </TabItem>
          <TabItem value="docker-compose" mdxType="TabItem">
            <p>{`compose!`}</p>
          </TabItem>
        </Tabs>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="service" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/setup/deployment/strategies/#service"
          }}>{`service deployment strategy`}</a>{` treats Vector like a
separate service. It is designed to receive data from an upstream source and
fan-out to one or more destinations.
Typically, upstream sources are other Vector instances sending data via the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sinks/vector/"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`vector`}</inlineCode>{` sink`}</a>{`, but can be collected through any of Vector's
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/"
          }}>{`sources`}</a>{`.
The following diagram demonstrates how it works.`}</p>
        <ServiceDiagram platformName={"docker"} sourceName={null} sinkName={null} mdxType="ServiceDiagram" />
        <hr></hr>
        <Tabs centered={true} className={"rounded"} defaultValue={"docker-cli"} placeholder="Please choose an installation method..." select={false} size={null} values={[{
          "group": "Platforms",
          "label": "Docker CLI",
          "value": "docker-cli"
        }, {
          "group": "Platforms",
          "label": "Docker Compose",
          "value": "docker-compose"
        }]} mdxType="Tabs">
          <TabItem value="docker-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
            <Steps headingDepth={3} mdxType="Steps">
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <h3 {...{
                    "id": "configure-vector-2"
                  }}>{`Configure Vector`}</h3>
                  <ConfigExample format="toml" path={"/etc/vector/vector.toml"} sourceName={"vector"} sinkName={null} mdxType="ConfigExample" />
                </li>
                <li>
                  <h3 {...{
                    "id": "start-the-vector-container-2"
                  }}>{`Start the Vector container`}</h3>
                  <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
                      "className": "language-bash"
                    }}>{`docker run \\
  -v $PWD/vector.toml:/etc/vector/vector.toml:ro \\
  -p 9000:9000 \\
  timberio/vector:latest-alpine
`}</code></pre>
                  <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
                    <ul>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`-v $PWD/vector.to...`}</inlineCode>{` flag passes your custom configuration to Vector.`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`-p 9000:9000`}</inlineCode>{` flag ensures that port 9000 is exposed for network communication.`}</li>
                      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`timberio/vector:latest-alpine`}</inlineCode>{` is the default image we've chosen, you are welcome to use `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                          "href": "/docs/setup/installation/platforms/docker/#variants"
                        }}>{`other image variants`}</a>{`.`}</li>
                    </ul>
                  </CodeExplanation>
                  <p>{`That's it! Simple and to the point. Hit `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`ctrl+c`}</inlineCode>{` to exit.`}</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </Steps>
          </TabItem>
          <TabItem value="docker-compose" mdxType="TabItem">
            <p>{`compose!`}</p>
          </TabItem>
        </Tabs>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "configuring"
    }}>{`Configuring`}</h2>
    <p>{`As shown above, you can pass a custom
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/"
      }}>{`Vector configuration file`}</a>{` via the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`-v`}</inlineCode>{` flag. You'll want
to do this since the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/timberio/vector/blob/master/config/vector.toml"
      }}>{`default `}<inlineCode parentName="a">{`/etc/vector/vector.toml`}</inlineCode>{` configuration file`}</a>{`
doesn't do anything.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "deploying"
    }}>{`Deploying`}</h2>
    <p>{`How you deploy Vector is largely dependent on your use case and environment.
Please see the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/deployment/"
      }}>{`deployment section`}</a>{` for more info on how to
deploy Vector.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "updating"
    }}>{`Updating`}</h2>
    <p>{`Simply run with newer version in the tag:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker pull timberio/vector:X.X.X-alpine && \\
  docker run timberio/vector:X.X.X-alpine
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`See the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#variants"
      }}>{`variants`}</a>{` and `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#versions"
      }}>{`versions`}</a>{` sections to choose
the appropriate image for your use case.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "images"
    }}>{`Images`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "variants"
    }}>{`Variants`}</h3>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "alpine"
    }}>{`alpine`}</h4>
    <p>{`This image is based on the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://hub.docker.com/_/alpine"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`alpine`}</inlineCode>{` Docker image`}</a>{`, which is
a Linux distribution built around musl libc and BusyBox. It is considerably
smaller in size than other Docker images and statically links libraries. This
is the image we recommend due to it's small size and reliability.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker run timberio/vector:0.9.2-alpine
`}</code></pre>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "debian"
    }}>{`debian`}</h4>
    <p>{`This image is based on the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://hub.docker.com/_/debian"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`debian-slim`}</inlineCode>{` image`}</a>{`,
which is a smaller, more compact variant of the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://hub.docker.com/_/debian"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`debian`}</inlineCode>{` image`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker run timberio/vector:0.9.2-debian
`}</code></pre>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "architectures"
    }}>{`Architectures`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector's images are multi-arch and support the
x86_64, ARM64, and ARMv7 architectures.
Docker handles this transparently for you.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "versions"
    }}>{`Versions`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector's Docker images can be downloaded with the following tags. Note that
Vector maintains special tags that are automatically updated whenever Vector is
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://vector.dev/releases/latest/"
      }}>{`released`}</a>{`:`}</p>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Version`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`URL`}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Latest major`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`timberio/vector:latest-alpine`}</inlineCode></td>
